This paper discusses the implementation of spatial search functions in Microsoft SQL Server 2005 using C# and table-valued functions. This topic falls under the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) categories. Additionally, the use of Hierarchical Triangular Mesh (HTM) algorithms from Johns Hopkins University suggests a potential connection to the graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV) categories. The implementation of spatial search functions also has applications in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for tasks such as location-based recommendation systems.
